reviews:
I stopped by this Thai restaurant in Cambridge, MA for a quick dinner. The ambiance was fairly standard—nothing particularly memorable. I ordered the red curry chicken with rice, and the food arrived impressively fast. The portion size was just right, and the curry was served piping hot—exactly how I like it.

That said, the curry sauce lacked richness. It was a bit too watery, and it seemed light on coconut milk, which left it feeling thin rather than full-bodied. Flavor-wise, it was decent, but didn’t quite hit the mark.

One downside was the the way green beans were cooked in the curry. There were plenty, but they were undercooked and overly crunchy, which threw off the texture of the dish. That detail alone kept this meal from earning five stars.
On a brighter note, the service was excellent—attentive and friendly throughout.

I ordered takeout for the first time

The food tasted great but my beef curry was very light

Pictured you can see the beef curry I ordered. The beef curry part of the meal was a pretty small portion and I was disappointed as it tasted fantastic.

I probably won't be ordering takeout in the future but I may try dining in to see if portions are better
Delicious food, great price, fast friendly service. Went for lunch on a Saturday afternoon, seated immediately, had food within 10 minutes. Nothing fancy but really hits the spot!

This restaurant appears to be an extension of a home, which is pretty cool. There's limited seating but it wasn't crowded when we stopped by for lunch on Sunday.

I ordered the Pad See Ew with a medium level of spice and it was pretty solid! I've tried a handful of thai restaurants in boston is this is one of the better ones I've had. Would recommend!
so it was not that good. i got the pad see ew and it was not very flavorful. noodles were very oily? the thai iced tea was good.
